00359 class SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES
00360 {
00361   public:
00362     friend class SecurityHelper;    
00364     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES() 
00365     {
00366         nSrtpKeyLength = 0 ;
00367         nSmimeKeyLength = 0 ;
00368         nSrtpLevel = SRTP_LEVEL_NONE ;
00369         memset(szSrtpKey, 0, sizeof(szSrtpKey));
00370         memset(szSmimeKeyDer, 0, sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer));
00371         memset(dbLocation, 0, sizeof(dbLocation));
00372         memset(szMyCertNickname, 0, sizeof(szMyCertNickname));
00373         memset(szCertDbPassword, 0, sizeof(szCertDbPassword));
00374     }    
00376     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00377     {
00378         copyData(ref);
00379     }    
00381     virtual ~SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES() { }    
00383     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& operator=(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00384     {
00385         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00386         copyData(ref);
00387         return *this;
00388     }    
00393     void setSrtpKey(const char* szKey, const int length)
00394     {
00395         int safeLen = (length < (int) sizeof(szSrtpKey)) ? length : (int) sizeof(szSrtpKey);
00396         memcpy(szSrtpKey, szKey, safeLen);
00397         nSrtpKeyLength = safeLen;
00398     }    
00403     void setSmimeKey(const char* szKey, const int length)
00404     {
00405         int safeLen = (length < (int) sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer)) ? length : (int) sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer);
00406         memcpy(szSmimeKeyDer, szKey, safeLen);
00407         nSmimeKeyLength = safeLen;
00408     }
00412     void setSecurityLevel(SIPX_SRTP_LEVEL security) { nSrtpLevel = security; }
00416     const char* getSrtpKey() const  { return szSrtpKey; }    
00421     const char* getSmimeKey() const { return szSmimeKeyDer; }
00425     const int getSrtpKeyLength() const  { return nSrtpKeyLength; }
00430     const int getSmimeKeyLength() const { return nSmimeKeyLength; }
00434     const int getSecurityLevel() const {return nSrtpLevel;}
00440     const char* getCertDbLocation() const { return dbLocation; }
00441   private:
00442     SIPX_SRTP_LEVEL nSrtpLevel;
00443     char szSrtpKey[MAX_SRTP_KEY_LENGTH];
00444     int  nSrtpKeyLength;    
00445     char szSmimeKeyDer[MAX_SMIME_KEY_LENGTH];
00446     int  nSmimeKeyLength; 
00447     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00448     char dbLocation[256];                         
00449     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00450     char szMyCertNickname[32];   
00451     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00452     char szCertDbPassword[MAX_PASSWORD_LENGTH];   
00453     void copyData(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00454     {
00455         nSrtpLevel = ref.nSrtpLevel;
00456         nSrtpKeyLength = ref.nSrtpKeyLength;
00457         nSmimeKeyLength = ref.nSmimeKeyLength;
00458         memcpy(szSrtpKey, ref.szSrtpKey, ref.nSrtpKeyLength);
00459         memcpy(szSmimeKeyDer, ref.szSmimeKeyDer, ref.nSmimeKeyLength);
00460         strncpy(dbLocation, ref.dbLocation, sizeof(dbLocation) - 1);
00461         strncpy(szMyCertNickname, ref.szMyCertNickname, sizeof(szMyCertNickname) - 1);
00462         strncpy(szCertDbPassword, ref.szCertDbPassword, sizeof(szCertDbPassword) - 1);
00463     }
00464 };

00515 struct SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY
00516 {
00518     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY()
00519     {
00520         cbSize = sizeof(SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY);
00521         type = SIPX_WINDOW_HANDLE_TYPE;
00522         handle = NULL;
00523     }
00525     ~SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY()
00526     {
00527         if (type == DIRECT_SHOW_FILTER)
00528         {
00529 #ifdef      _WIN32
00530             if (handle) ((IUnknown*)handle)->Release();
00531 #endif              
00532         }
00533     }
00534     
00536     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00537     {
00538         copy(ref);
00539     }
00541     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& operator=(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00542     {
00543         // check for assignment to self
00544         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00545         copy(ref);
00546         return *this;
00547     }    
00548         
00549     int cbSize;                     
00550     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY_TYPE type;   
00551     union
00552     {
00553         SIPX_WINDOW_HANDLE handle;  
00554         IBaseFilter* filter;        
00555     };
00556 private:
00557     void copy(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00558     {
00559         cbSize = ref.cbSize;
00560         type = ref.type;
00561         handle = ref.handle;
00562         if (type == DIRECT_SHOW_FILTER)
00563         {
00564 #ifdef      _WIN32
00565             // we should addRef here.
00566             if (handle) ((IBaseFilter*)handle)->AddRef();
00567 #endif            
00568         }
00569     }
00570     
00571 };

00585 struct SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS
00586 {
00588     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS()
00589     {
00590         memset((void*)cInterface, 0, sizeof(cInterface));
00591         memset((void*)cIpAddress, 0, sizeof(cIpAddress));
00592         memset((void*)cCustomTransportName, 0, sizeof(cCustomTransportName));
00593         memset((void*)cCustomRouteID, 0, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00594         eContactType = CONTACT_AUTO;
00595         eTransportType = TRANSPORT_UDP ;
00596         id = 0;
00597         iPort = -1;
00598     }
00600     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS(const SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& ref)
00601     {
00602         strcpy(cInterface, ref.cInterface);
00603         strcpy(cIpAddress, ref.cIpAddress);
00604         eContactType = ref.eContactType;
00605         eTransportType = ref.eTransportType;
00606         id = ref.id;
00607         iPort = ref.iPort;
00608         strncpy(cCustomTransportName, ref.cCustomTransportName, 32);
00609         strncpy(cCustomRouteID, ref.cCustomRouteID, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00610     }
00612     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& operator=(const SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& ref)
00613     {
00614         // check for assignment to self
00615         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00616         strcpy(cInterface, ref.cInterface);
00617         strcpy(cIpAddress, ref.cIpAddress);
00618         eContactType = ref.eContactType;
00619         eTransportType = ref.eTransportType;
00620         id = ref.id;
00621         iPort = ref.iPort;
00622         strncpy(cCustomTransportName, ref.cCustomTransportName, sizeof(cCustomTransportName));
00623         strncpy(cCustomRouteID, ref.cCustomRouteID, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00624         return *this;
00625     }    
00626     
00627     SIPX_CONTACT_ID     id;              
00628     SIPX_CONTACT_TYPE   eContactType ;   
00629     SIPX_TRANSPORT_TYPE eTransportType ; 
00630     char                cInterface[32] ; 
00631     char                cIpAddress[32] ; 
00632     int                 iPort ;          
00633     char                cCustomTransportName[32]; 
00634     char                cCustomRouteID[64] ;
00635 };
